# contentMayVary

**Instance Property**

A Boolean value that indicates whether an event’s content is dynamic and the server may respond with different interstitial assets for other participants in a coordinated playback session.

## Declaration

```swift
var contentMayVary: Bool { get set }
```

## Discussion

If the value is [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false], the primary asset participates in coordinated playback, this event does as well.

The default value is [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true].

## Inspecting timeline occupancy

- **timelineOccupancy**: An event’s occupancy on the integrated timeline.
- **AVPlayerInterstitialEvent.TimelineOccupancy**: Constants that specify how an event occupies time on an integrated timeline.
- **supplementsPrimaryContent**: A Boolean value that indicates whether an event supplements the primary content and should present with the primary item.
- **plannedDuration**: The planned duration of the event.
